citation.case_name: City of Sherrill, New York v. Oneida Indian Nation of New York

html_with_citations:
543 U.S. 953

CITY OF SHERRILL, NEW YORK
v.
ONEIDA INDIAN NATION OF NEW YORK ET AL.

No. 03-855.

Supreme Court of United States.

November 1, 2004.

1

C. A. 2d Cir. [Certiorari granted, 542 U. S. 936.] Motion of New York for leave to participate in oral argument as amicus curiae and for divided argument granted. Motion of the Acting Solicitor General for leave to participate in oral argument as amicus curiae and for divided argument granted.
